'''Level 27.3''' is a sublevel of [[Level 27]]. </span>
{{Blurimage|file=Fan basement blue.webp|caption=Image of what appears to be one of the upper floors of Level 27.3.}}
== Description: ==
<span style="color:#000000;">'''Level 27.3''' resembles an interminable commercial basement seemingly built in the 1980's. The building seems to have been stripped clean of all furniture and has minor damage and paint chipping. The walls appear to be wooden, and the floor is covered in blue-gray carpet. '''Level 27.3''' is fully vented and the ventilation is active despite the level's state. This puts '''Level 27.3''' in a mildly chilly climate with ventilation buzzing being a constant. It is exclusively lit by lights connected to fans. This light is dim and the bulbs are often damaged by water. Hallways will occasionally run between the rooms, connected to them by doors but they have no lighting whatsoever. 

<span style="color:#000000;">Practically the only real danger of '''Level 27.3''' is its lack of supplies. It is devoid of any items, useful or dangerous aside from the basic construction materials of the complex. These materials are also noted to be of poor quality and often water-damaged. The level spans multiple floors with stairs connecting them. '''Level 27.3''''s higher floors tend to have varied carpets, more exits, and are in better condition whilst the lower ones may be heavily damaged. Several abnormal rooms have been found which contain different floor styles and wallpaper. These rooms are very scattered and often are the only source of any usable material on '''Level 27.3''', often small scraps of supplies. 
{{Blurimage|file=Lookslikeligneous.jpg|caption=An anomalous room within Level 27.3 resembling its host level.}}

<span style="color:#000000;"> The most notable property of '''Level 27.3''' is its inability for anyone to remember going there. This will specifically only occur upon exiting the level and only affects the memory of traveling there. This means details about '''Level 27.3''' are still known, although they're believed by the wanderer to be from alternative sources. Individuals can be told of their entry into '''Level 27.3''' but are often adverse to taking it seriously. It is unknown if this is a property of '''Level 27.3''' or just a natural reaction. As such it is recommended to log any entrances and experiences into '''Level 27.3'''. 

<span style="color:#000000;"> The only other cataloged property is messages scrawled onto the walls of '''Level 27.3''' via a variety of methods. (Marker, paint chipping, dried blood, and human teeth are all common). It is unknown when these messages appear, but it is verifiable that they can appear in already mapped areas. Many of these messages are noted to appear on the paths of wanderers, often with delay. In one case it was reported that a wanderer fell asleep only to wake up to one of these messages. Wanderers often report feelings of intense dread from the rooms near and around these messages. 
{{Blurimage|file=Blue carpet fan room.jpg|caption= }}

== Entities: ==
<span style="color:#000000;"> '''Level 27.3''' has no known entities and is highly suspected to be deserted. Reports of various effects are most likely hallucinations brought on by low sanity or high amounts of stress. 
== '''''Bases and Outposts''''' ==
<span style="color:#000000;"> '''Level 27.3''' is generally considered to be very hard to inhabit. Anything established can only be sustained by imports of vital resources. It is strongly to establish any outposts in easily locatable areas with proximity to entrances and exits.

=== [[B.W.O.]] Material Outpost ===
* <span style="color:#000000;">Minor construction material gathering base.
* <span style="color:#000000;">Friendly and actively helpful to Wanderers. 
* <span style="color:#000000;"> <s>7</s> 6 permanent members
* <span style="color:#000000;"> Maintained by regular supply shipments
* <span style="color:#000000;"> '''Editor's Note:''' ''I recommend whichever troll keeps adjusting the member count cease immediately.''

== Entrances and Exits ==
=== Entrances ===
* <span style="color:#000000;"> Descending a staircase behind a door on [[Level 27]] will lead one here. 
=== Exits ===
* <span style="color:#000000;"> Uncarpeted Staircases will lead back to [[Level 27]].
* <span style="color:#000000;"> Finding a door in a naturally dark room will lead to [[Level 462]].  
